	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well we just did this last night (2/19/2002) for myself and another SK.  We tried 1 group with a 53 SK, 52 SK, high lvl cleric, 47 warrior, and a druid.  It was a near total group wipeout.  First, the mob does NOT respond to Dark/Fear.  Neither would stick and the mob was an even con to one of the SKs!  Anti-undead DDs however do work, so I used Expulse Undead.  The mob did NOT poof when we failed to kill it, so we got a 2nd group going with 2 mid 50's necros, 2 mid 50's rangers, and a druid.  With those 2 groups we killed the mob twice in a row.  If you fail to kill it and have to regroup the Monstrous Zombie will heal up and recharge it's HT.  The HT is strong enough to take a cleric buffed 53 SK down to about 1/2 a bub of health, and it pretty much killed a lvl 55 ranger instantly (mob may have hit him once but that's it).<BR>
<BR>
FYI the spell scroll is not no drop, though I don't know if you can get the quest if you're not a SHD.  Also, the Pulsating talisman is 7 INT &amp; 7 AGI neck for SHD/NEC, not bad on its' own for a necro.<BR>
<BR>
FYI also, the first time we completed the quest Kazeel poofed as expected, but he immediately respawned on a mountain top near some standing stones in the same valley, so you can do this spell in succession for several SKs as long as they all have their Pulsating talismans ready to go.  Just med betweeen turn-ins.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
